From 3bfaa05651ce89af49c4803e4795feeaef9c88b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tom Zanussi <tom.zanussi@linux.intel.com>
Date: Tue, 19 Sep 2017 10:39:20 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 65/66] tracing: Add inter-event blurb to HIST_TRIGGERS config
 option

So that users know that inter-event tracing is supported as part of
the HIST_TRIGGERS option, include text to that effect in the help
text.

Signed-off-by: Tom Zanussi <tom.zanussi@linux.intel.com>
---
 kernel/trace/Kconfig | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/trace/Kconfig b/kernel/trace/Kconfig
index e97993f..53abe81 100644
--- a/kernel/trace/Kconfig
+++ b/kernel/trace/Kconfig
@@ -596,7 +596,10 @@ config HIST_TRIGGERS
 	  event activity as an initial guide for further investigation
 	  using more advanced tools.
 
-	  See Documentation/trace/events.txt.
+	  Inter-event tracing of quantities such as latencies is also
+	  supported using hist triggers under this option.
+
+	  See Documentation/trace/histogram.txt.
 	  If in doubt, say N.
 
 config MMIOTRACE_TEST
